const sourceCode = "# API Overview\n\nClearSight exposes a REST API for all operations. The Next.js app serves both the UI and the API.\n\n## Base URL\n\n```\nhttp://localhost:3000/api\n```\n\n## Endpoints\n\n### Scans (Single-Page)\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| `POST` | `/api/scans` | Create a single-page scan |\n| `GET` | `/api/scans` | List scans (paginated) |\n| `GET` | `/api/scans/:id` | Get scan status/results |\n| `POST` | `/api/scans/:id/cancel` | Cancel a running scan |\n| `GET` | `/api/scans/:id/export?format=pdf\\|excel` | Export scan report |\n\n### Sites\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| `POST` | `/api/sites` | Create site (or return existing) |\n| `GET` | `/api/sites` | List all sites |\n| `GET` | `/api/sites/:id` | Get site detail |\n| `DELETE` | `/api/sites/:id` | Delete site and all data |\n\n### Crawls\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| `POST` | `/api/sites/:id/crawl` | Start a new crawl |\n| `GET` | `/api/sites/:id/crawls` | List crawls (paginated) |\n| `GET` | `/api/sites/:id/crawls/:crawlId` | Get crawl detail |\n| `POST` | `/api/sites/:id/crawls/:crawlId/cancel` | Cancel a crawl |\n\n### Pages\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| `GET` | `/api/sites/:id/pages` | List pages (paginated) |\n| `GET` | `/api/sites/:id/pages/:pageId` | Get page detail |\n\n### Issues\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| `GET` | `/api/sites/:id/issues` | List issues (filterable) |\n| `PATCH` | `/api/sites/:id/issues/:issueId` | Update issue status |\n\n## Pagination\n\nList endpoints support `limit` and `offset` query parameters:\n\n```bash\nGET /api/scans?limit=20&offset=0\nGET /api/sites/:id/pages?limit=50&offset=0\n```\n\n## Filtering (Issues)\n\nThe issues endpoint supports these query parameters:\n\n| Parameter | Values | Description |\n|-----------|--------|-------------|\n| `severity` | `critical`, `serious`, `moderate`, `minor` | Filter by severity |\n| `wcagLevel` | `A`, `AA` | Filter by WCAG level |\n| `status` | `open`, `fixed`, `dismissed`, `cant_fix` | Filter by issue status |\n| `pageId` | UUID | Filter by specific page |\n\n## Rate Limiting\n\n- Single-page scans: 10 per hour per IP\n- Crawl creation: 1 concurrent crawl per site\n- Intra-crawl page scans bypass IP rate limits";
