const sourceCode = "# Getting Started\n\nClearSight scans websites for WCAG 2.1 Level A and AA accessibility violations, enriches findings with AI, and delivers actionable reports.\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n- A running ClearSight instance (see [deployment docs](/deployment))\n- A website URL to scan\n\n## Your First Scan\n\n### Quick Single-Page Scan\n\n1. Open the **Dashboard**\n2. Enter a URL in the scan form (e.g., `https://example.com`)\n3. Click **Scan**\n4. Wait for the pipeline to complete (~30-60 seconds per page)\n5. Review your results\n\n### Full Site Crawl\n\n1. Open the **Dashboard**\n2. Enter your site URL — ClearSight will create a Site record\n3. Navigate to the Site Overview page\n4. Click **Crawl Now**\n5. Watch the live progress as pages are discovered and scanned\n6. Review aggregated results across all pages\n\n## Understanding Results\n\nAfter a scan completes, you'll see:\n\n- **Score** — 0-100 accessibility score\n- **Issues** — categorized as Confirmed or Potential\n- **Severity** — Critical, Serious, Moderate, or Minor\n- **AI Summary** — overview of your page's accessibility\n- **Fix Suggestions** — actionable steps for each issue\n- **Visual Inspector** — see the exact element on a screenshot\n\n## Next Steps\n\n- Learn about [single-page scanning](/scanning/single-page)\n- Set up [full-site crawling](/scanning/full-site-crawl)\n- Understand [issue tracking](/scanning/issue-tracking)";
