const sourceCode = "# ClearSight Documentation\n\nWelcome to the ClearSight documentation. ClearSight is an AI-powered WCAG 2.1 accessibility checker that crawls your entire site and delivers actionable results.\n\n## Quick Start\n\n1. Go to the [Dashboard](/dashboard)\n2. Enter your site URL\n3. Click **Start scanning** — ClearSight will crawl every page\n4. Review your results with AI-generated fix suggestions\n\n## What ClearSight Does\n\n- **Full-site crawling** — discovers every page via BFS link following + sitemap parsing\n- **WCAG 2.1 A & AA checks** — 50+ axe-core rules plus custom engines\n- **AI enrichment** — human-readable descriptions and fix suggestions for every issue\n- **Issue tracking** — track new, fixed, and recurring issues across crawls\n- **Export** — PDF reports with executive summaries and Excel spreadsheets\n\n## Sections\n\n- [Getting Started](/getting-started) — first scan walkthrough\n- [Scanning](/scanning/single-page) — single-page and full-site scanning\n- [Results](/results/understanding-scores) — scores, issues, and inspector\n- [API Reference](/api/overview) — REST API documentation\n- [FAQ](/faq) — common questions";
