const sourceCode = "# Issue Types and Severity\n\nClearSight categorizes every finding by type and severity.\n\n## Issue Types\n\n### Confirmed\n\nDefinite WCAG violations detected automatically. These are issues that the scanner can identify with certainty — for example, an image with no `alt` attribute.\n\n### Potential\n\nIssues flagged for human review. The scanner suspects a violation but can't be certain without manual verification — for example, an image with alt text that may not adequately describe the image content.\n\n## Severity Levels\n\n| Severity | Color | Description |\n|----------|-------|-------------|\n| **Critical** | Red | Blocks access for users with disabilities. Fix immediately. |\n| **Serious** | Orange | Significantly degrades the experience. Fix as priority. |\n| **Moderate** | Yellow | Creates barriers for some users. Should be addressed. |\n| **Minor** | Blue | Best practice violation. Low impact but worth fixing. |\n\n## WCAG Criteria\n\nEach issue references a specific WCAG 2.1 success criterion (e.g., `1.1.1 Non-text Content`) and conformance level:\n\n- **Level A** — minimum accessibility requirements\n- **Level AA** — standard compliance target (most legal frameworks require this)\n\n## Confidence Score\n\nAI enrichment assigns a confidence score (0-100) to each issue, indicating how certain the system is about the finding. Higher scores mean more definitive violations.\n\n## Engines\n\nIssues come from three engines:\n\n1. **axe-core** — industry-standard accessibility testing library (50+ rules)\n2. **LinkTextEngine** — custom checks for empty or non-descriptive link text\n3. **TouchTargetEngine** — custom checks for minimum touch target sizing (48x48px)";
