const sourceCode = "# Understanding Scores\n\nClearSight assigns a 0-100 accessibility score to each scanned page and aggregates them at the site level.\n\n## Page Score\n\nEach page gets an individual score based on the number and severity of issues found. The score is generated by AI analysis considering:\n\n- Total number of issues\n- Severity distribution (critical issues weigh more heavily)\n- Issue types (confirmed violations vs potential issues)\n\n### Score Ranges\n\n| Score | Label | Color | Meaning |\n|-------|-------|-------|---------|\n| 80-100 | Good | Green | Few or minor issues |\n| 50-79 | Needs Work | Yellow | Significant issues to address |\n| 0-49 | Poor | Red | Critical accessibility barriers |\n\n## Site Score\n\nThe site-level score is the **average of all page scores** from the latest crawl. This gives you a holistic view of your site's accessibility.\n\n## Score Over Time\n\nBy running multiple crawls, you can track your score trajectory. Each crawl stores its overall score, so you can see improvement (or regression) in the crawl history.\n\n## Fallback Scoring\n\nIf AI enrichment fails, ClearSight uses a simple heuristic: start at 100, subtract 5 points per issue. This ensures you always get a score even when the LLM is unavailable.";
