const sourceCode = "# Single-Page Scan\n\nScan a single URL for WCAG 2.1 accessibility violations without creating a site or running a full crawl.\n\n## How It Works\n\n1. Enter a URL in the Dashboard scan form\n2. ClearSight renders the page in headless Chromium (1280x720)\n3. axe-core runs 50+ WCAG 2.1 A/AA checks\n4. Custom engines check link text quality and touch target sizing\n5. AI enriches each issue with descriptions and fix suggestions\n6. Results display with an overall score\n\n## Pipeline Stages\n\n| Stage | Progress | What Happens |\n|-------|----------|-------------|\n| Fetch | 20% | Playwright renders the page, captures screenshot |\n| Analyze | 40% | axe-core accessibility checks |\n| Custom Checks | 55% | Link text + touch target engines |\n| Element Locate | 65% | Bounding boxes for visual inspection |\n| Intermediate Store | 70% | Preliminary results saved (preview visible) |\n| Enrich | 80% | AI generates descriptions and fix suggestions |\n| Store | 100% | Final results saved |\n\n## Progressive Results\n\nYou don't have to wait for the full pipeline. After the Intermediate Store stage (70%), you'll see preliminary results with basic descriptions. The AI enrichment runs in the background and upgrades the results in-place.\n\n## API\n\n```bash\n# Create a single-page scan\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/scans \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"url\": \"https://example.com\"}'\n\n# Poll for results\ncurl http://localhost:3000/api/scans/{scanId}\n```\n\n## Rate Limiting\n\nSingle-page scans are rate-limited to 10 per hour per IP address.";
